  <prompt>
    Close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T028-07** by fixing the Upload endpoint binding/exception path. 9 integration tests in `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/Api/Ai/UploadIntegrationTests.cs` fail with `HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError (500)` instead of the documented `422 UnprocessableEntity` / `200 OK` / `204 NoContent`.

    🚨 **STEP 0 GATE**: Before any code change, **verify whether task 011 (Phase 1 RB-T028-03/04/05/06 cluster fix) already resolved this entry**. The ledger §812-852 hypothesizes the same root cause as the Phase 1 cluster: conditional service registration + unconditional endpoint mapping. Run `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~UploadIntegrationTests"` BEFORE fixing — if all 9 tests now pass (i.e., the Phase 1 root-cause fix subsumes this entry), close RB-T028-07 with mode `repaired-by-cluster` cross-referencing task 011 commit SHA. NO further code change needed.

    If still failing: apply the ledger §841-844 recommended two-step fix:
    1. **Exception isolation**: wrap the file-validation block in try/catch and return `Results.UnprocessableEntity()` / `Results.BadRequest()` for known-rejection cases. Don't let validation errors fall through to ASP.NET Core's 500 handler.
    2. **Storage seam**: introduce an `IUploadStorage` (or use `IBlobStore` if it exists) abstraction so the test fixture can register an in-memory implementation that succeeds on Accept-* cases.

    Per NFR-04 cite `RB-T028-07` + resolution mode (`repaired` OR `repaired-by-cluster`). Per ADR-010 + ADR-018: if conditional registration is the cause, prefer **unconditional service registration** when the endpoint is mapped unconditionally (the rule codified by Phase 1 task 011).
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent verifying + (conditionally) fixing the Upload endpoint binding/exception path.</role>

  <goal>
    All 9 tests in `UploadIntegrationTests.cs` pass without Skip. EITHER closed as `repaired-by-cluster` (cross-referencing task 011) if Phase 1 fix subsumed this entry, OR closed as `repaired` with the new exception-isolation + storage-seam fix applied.
  </goal>

